// ISSUE TITLE: Server accepts unlimited chunk requests causing high memory usage
// ISSUE REPORT:
### Steps to Reproduce and Observed Behavior

When a player joins with high render distance, RAM spikes significantly.

Example:
- Player with RD 8 -> ~16,000 chunks -> ~1.5GB RAM
- Player with RD 12 -> ~52.000 chunks -> ~7GB RAM


In **src/network/protocols.zig**, **chunkRequest.serverReceive()** accepts all chunk requests without limit:
```
while (reader.remaining.len >= 4) {
    conn.user.?.increaseRefCount();
    main.server.world.?.queueChunkAndDecreaseRefCount(request, conn.user.?);
}
```

I see **queueChunkAndDecreaseRefCount** uses **isStillNeeded()** to filter tasks, but all 52,000 tasks are still created and allocated before filtering happens.

// DISCUSSION:
[MAINTAINER COMMENT]
The memory footprint of these tasks is on the order of maybe 1 megabyte. What you are observing in memory usage is the effect of the caches growing. Past ~8 GB you will only see small increases with more people joining.

