// ISSUE TITLE: Use bloom filter for searching tags
// ISSUE REPORT:
[Bloom filter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bloom_filter) could be used to probabilistically improve search time when checking if block/item has a specific tag.
It is expected that list of tags will grow as we will need them for grouping items and blocks in various ways, so linear search which is not a problem now may become one in the future.

// DISCUSSION:
[MAINTAINER COMMENT]
You know I actually thought about this a bit after we talked, and I've come to the conclusion that it's not worth it.

The bloom filter is mainly relevant for large datasets that are expensive to compare, but we have a small dataset (currently only 1 or 2) of integers.
If we use the index space as the bloom filter, it might make it faster, but it adds a lot of code complexity.

And if we properly align and over-allocate the buffer, we would be able to do it in one SIMD operation for most blocks/items, since it's unlikely we'll see more than 8 (16 for AVX-512) tags.

