// ISSUE TITLE: Infer `cubyz:` prefix if results in valid ID
// ISSUE REPORT:
In Pattern and Mask expressions `cubyz:` prefix is redundant most of the time - IDs can be identified unambiguously without it because there is only one `stone` ID, `cubyz:stone`. Proposal is to allow infering `cubyz:` prefix if it results in valid ID. There is only disadvantage of such approach - in expressions without addon name data segment must also be omitted, otherwise ID of a block would be interpreted as addon name.

// DISCUSSION:
[MAINTAINER COMMENT]
This seems like it's just a workaround for the fact that there is no autocomplete for commands yet.

