[MAINTAINER COMMENT]
There is a semantic difference between those two forms. If I remember correctly`@import` is relative to current file, so referencing file in a different parent directory is at least awkward.
`main.x` gives x a stable root, instead of relative one. Again, if I remember correctly main is a special case here, due to some part of building config. 
The one and only valid approach is to import public stuff to main, but this is a huge time investment and it's not good for prototyping (alpha) stage we are in. This would guarantee controlled public interface, but for that to make sense we would have to respect that interface.

I think a more actionable issue is to eliminate cases where we use same eg. Struct used both as `mod.Struct` and through aliased `Struct`. Rest is far future.

