// ISSUE TITLE: [SBB] Block substitution in blueprints used by SBBs
// ISSUE REPORT:
## Drescription

Allow block substitution in blueprints with use of masks (#1284) and patterns (#1237).
Substitution mapping can be specified as part of SBB definition
Substitution will be automatically inherited by all children structures **unless** `inherit_substitutions` is set to `false`.
Substitutions will be expressed with list of dictionaries containing `new` and `old` keys to avoid ambiguity caused by using plain hash map. (As discussed while implementing migrations)

```zig
.{
	.blueprint = "cubyz:generator",
	.substitute = .{
		.{.old = "cubyz:birch_log", .new = "cubyz:oak_log"},
	}
	.inherit_substitutions = false,
	.children = .{
		.crimson = .{
			.{.structure = "cubyz:tree/birch/1/tree/1", .chance = 0.2},
			.{.structure = "cubyz:tree/birch/1/tree/2", .chance = 0.2},
			.{.structure = "cubyz:tree/birch/1/tree/3", .chance = 0.2},
			.{.structure = "cubyz:tree/birch/1/tree/4", .chance = 0.4},
		},
	},
}
```

## TBD

- Should it be allowed for children structure to define substitution map if parent structure contains one?
- Should blueprints with substituted blocks be cached in HashMap to avoid duplicating identical blueprints?
  - What should be the key structure? eg. `struct { old: []const u8, new: []const u8 }`

// DISCUSSION:
[MAINTAINER COMMENT]
> Should it be allowed for children structure to define substitution map if parent structure contains one?

Maybe we should only allow them at a higher level, outside the SBBs.

[MAINTAINER COMMENT]
@ikabod-kee will not be happy, they are not keen on copying SBB use multiple times in biome definition (instead using dedicated generator SBBs that aggregate multiple tree models), not even considering something as verbose as substitution map. Likely one would have to duplicate it for multiple biomes too which is not fun idea even for me.

If we were to go with special SBB "generators" category as proposed in https://github.com/PixelGuys/Cubyz/issues/1408#issuecomment-2855170261 we could restrict substitution maps only to those, alongside `snap` parameter.

